ume practitioners will find not only an indispensable introduction to new forms of assessment but also a number of best practices as described by experienced educators.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDistance educationxEvaluation. 7aEDUCATION / Distance, Open & Online Education.2bisacsh  amoodle, LMS, MOOC, cheating, constructivism, e-portfolios, group work, open education, blended learning.1 aOpeno, Jason, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771992336423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771992336/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles